<v-card-title class="text-h3">PART</v-card-title>
<v-row justify="center"> <v-card-title class="text-h4 title">Overview  </v-card-title></v-row>
<v-card-text>  <p class = "body-1">Since MIBOM comes from a multi-system design, the parts we've built to support the project are quite diverse and fascinating. Our parts are mainly concentrated in the adhesive system and the regulatory system. We carefully submitted the components we developed to perform one specific function into <u>**Basic Part**</u> in **<u>Registry</u>**, then each basic part is meaningfully combined with others to compose functional **<u>Composite Parts</u>**, and finally submitted in **<u>Registry</u>**.</p>
</v-card-text><v-card-title class="text-h5">Basic Parts</v-card-title>
<v-card-text>  <p class = "body-1">| Name                                                    | Short Description                              | Long Description                                             |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| ------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755006](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755006) | mouse Piezo1.1                                 | A splicing variant of mPiezo1 which is more sensitive to mechanical stimulation. |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755007](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755007) | GCaMP6m                                        | A genetically encoded calcium indicator                      |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755010](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755010) | NFAT response element                          | NFAT can bind to this part to activate downstream gene transicription. |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa K3755013](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755013) | Alginate lyase with human IL-2 signal sequence | Alginate lyase can degrade alginate. With human IL-2 signal sequence, secretion of the alginate lyase in mammalian cells can be achieved. |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755018](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755018) | IL2-algH-EGFP                                  | This is a fusion protein that consist of an alginate lyase with human IL-2 signal sequence and EGFP. |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755015](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755015) | mRuby2 red fluorescent protein                 | monomeric red fluorescent protein derived from mRuby, with improved photophysical properties |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755002](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755002) | Mfp5 CDS                                       | Recombinant mussel foot protein coding sequence, isolated from Mytilus galloprovincialis, expressed in *E.coli* BL21. |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755003](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755003) | 2\*Mfp5 CDS                                    | Two consecutive recombinant mussel foot protein type-5 coding sequences, isolated from Mytilus galloprovincialis, expressed in *E.coli* BL21. |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755021](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755021) | linker for Mfp5 CDS&His tag                    | The linker connecting His tag to Mfps CDS, containing BioBrick cut sites |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755004](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755004) | cfa-N                                          | Codon optimized N-terminal spontaneous splicing−ligation peptide sequnece for 3\*Mfp5 CDS assembly, connected downstream of the 2\*Mfp5 CDS |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755005](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755005) | cfa-C                                          | Codon optimized C-terminal spontaneous splicing−ligation peptide sequnece for 3\*Mfp5 CDS assembly, connected downstream of the Mfp5 CDS |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755009](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755009) | AKTK expression tag                            | To increase translation initiation rates for protein expression |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755022](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755022) | hSyn promoter                                  | Human synapsin I promoter，confers neuron-specific expression |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755025](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755025) | loxP site-1                                    | A sequence containing a Lox2272 site and a LoxP site, which can be recognized by Cyclization Recombinatation Enzyme(CRE), upstream of GCaMP6m in pAAV.Syn.Flex.GCaMP6m.WPRE.SV40 |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755026](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755026) | loxP site-2                                    | A sequence containing a Lox2272 site and a LoxP site, which can be recognized by Cyclization Recombinatation Enzyme(CRE), downstream of GCaMP6m in pAAV.Syn.Flex.GCaMP6m.WPRE.SV40 |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755027](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755027) | WPRE                                           | Woodchuck hepatitis virus posttranscriptional regulatory element |</p>
<p class = "body-1">| [BBa_K3755020](http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_K3755020) | 6*His tag                                      | Attached to the upstream or downstream of the protein, used to bind the protein to the medium in nickel ion affinity chromatography during the protein purification |</p>
</v-card-text><v-card-title class="text-h5">Composite Parts</v-card-title>
